dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor not out 118 (125b 7x4 4x6 181m) SR: 94.4
Elton Chigumbura c Mushfiqur Rahim b Mahmudullah 38 (38b 6x4 0x6 48m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: quicker delivery outside the off stump, Chigumbara had no option but to play at it and he ends up with a thin edge. Rahim makes no mistake behind the stumps. Zimbabwe 3 down

headshotImage.caption: Forster Mutizwa player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Forster Mutizwa player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: tossed up on the stump, Mutizwa looks to work it away on the leg side but ends up with a leading edge back to the bowler. 4 more to go.

Two wickets in three balls -  second time this has happened today! Shakib fires it outside the off stump, Chibhabha pushes forward to defend and the edge is taken. Junaid at first slip dives low to his left and takes a super catch - Chibhabha departs for a duck

headshotImage.caption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: and the drop off the previous ball does not count for much as Vermeulen looks to run the ball down to third man but only succeeds in edging it to first slip. It takes a diving effort from Junaid to hold onto the catch. Good catch that! Predictably the happiest man around is Rahim

and "Junaid-man" is in action again as Razzak bowls one spinning away from the batsman. Masakadza is deceived in the flight as he comes down the track but decides to go through with the drive on the leg side. All he manages to get is an edge that flies fast to first slip where Junaid leaps across to his right and snips it mid-air. What a catch! and he has two of them to show off now

image.longCaption: Ray Price portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalComment.html: gone! 9 down with Taylor on 99! slightly short and on the stumps, the ball just skidded through after hitting the deck, Price leans back to pull and is beaten all ends up. Loud appeal and up goes the finger

Mahmudullah run out (Chibhabha) 33 (53b 1x4 1x6 73m) SR: 62.26

dismissalComment.html: is that a run-out? The Zimbabweans are confident, the batsman was well short at the non-striker's end when the stumps were broken, but did the bowler's hands disturb the stumps before that? it was turned to backward square leg, the batsmen looked to pinch a tight single, the replays showed that it was the ball that hit the stumps, Mahmudullah was well short, he's on his way, is there a twist in this game?
Cremer takes the catch at backward square leg, it was a short ball, Mushfiqur goes for the sweep, top-edges it

Matsikenyeri has done it, superb delivery, Shakib is going down the track looking to smash the ball out of the ground, he doesn't connect as the ball spins away sharply, Taylor has ages to whip off the bails, no need for a third umpire this time

dismissalComment.html: Chibhabha has struck, a pretty poor delivery, angling down leg, Razzak helps it along to the keeper Mutizwa, who's standing in for Taylor, who has gone off the field

yes he can, that's a double-wicket maiden, fantastic over for Zimbabwe, Enamul was a bit unlucky as that hit him above the knee-roll in front of middle and leg, might have been worth giving him the benefit of doubt there, the umpire has raised his finger though

dismissalComment.html: yorker from Mpofu, superb delivery that,  Naeem just about squeezed it out towards the keeper, the batsmen went through for the single, Tamim seemed to have got in the bowler's way, he caught short by the keeper's throw, he stands his ground protesting that the bowler blocked him, the umpire sends him on his way, massive blow for Bangladesh

commentTextItems.html: Naeem has done it, sensational victory for Bangladesh, what a mature innings this is from Naeem, it would have all ended in tears though if the fielder at extra cover had thrown down the stumps at the non-striker's stumps when Naeem was scampering the single, the ball ricocheted off the bowler's hand to reach extra cover, the crowd is delirious and why not?

commentPostTextItems.html: Who'd have thought the dead rubber would turn out to be the most exciting match of the series? The game swung from one team to the other, both sides scrapping hard for the advantage. Bangladesh looked in trouble when Shakib got out at 105 but Mahmudullah and Naeem brought them back with a fighting partnership. Zimbabwe seized the upper hand again by taking four wickets for 13 runs, but a memorable innings from Naeem sealed the victory for the home side. They are going to be talking about those three consecutive sixes for a long time in Chittagong.

Hamilton Masakadza "I thought we couldn't control the game today though Brendan Taylor scored a century in the morning. I thought the guys fought hard, tried hard but that one over which went for 18-20 runs changed things. We have picked up a lot on this tour, we should improve from here. The crowds have been really great both here and in Dhaka."

The Man of the Match is, unsurprisingly, Naeem Islam. "Yeah, I really enjoyed the innings. When me and Riyad were batting, we thought if we continue like this we will win easily. Even after his wicket, Tamim was there so I thought we could win. Right till the end I never thought we would lose."

The Man of the Series is Abdur Razzak for his 15 wickets. "It's really important that the team also does well. If I do well, and the team doesn't that is not satisfying. This game was a little tight, Naeem did a very good job, Nazmul as well. We have domestic cricket coming up, which we have to play so there's no rest."

Shakib Al Hasan "Naeem played really well. Some of our guys had the confidence that if we had a good over Naeem could do it. We need to take some responsibility, especially our top order and middle order because our bowlers did very well through the series. Both Chittagong and Dhaka crowds have been excellent."
Shakib holds the trophy aloft after Bangladesh pull off a convincing 4-1 series victory.
That's it from us at Cricinfo for this series, thanks for joining us. There's another match going on right now, India v Australia. Hop on.

commentTextItems.html: another short ball, this outside off, Naeem calmly gets under that one as well
Mpofu surprises him with bouncer, Naeem spots it early and ducks under
score are level, not the most convincing of strokes from Naeem, it was a ytorker length ball just outside off, gets a thick outside edge past the keeper for four
slightly shorter, Naeem drives it elegantly towards extra cover, another single turned down
in the blockhole, on off and middle, dug out to the leg side, good delivery that
gets the single to keep the strike, Naeem was looking to whip that to the leg side, gets it away to mid-off

commentTextItems.html: well outside off, Naeem looks to make it four in a row, but that was too wide to swipe to the leg side
A hat-trick of sixes, Naeem Islam is going berserk here, Chibhabha not learning his lessons, offers a length ball again, Naeem smashes it over wide long-on for another six
wow, what a shot that is, another length ball, Naeem gets under it and whacks it over the bowler's head for another six
Naeem dances down the track and launches that on over long-on for a six to bring up his half-century, that was a length ball
powers it to long-on, easy single for the taking, doesn't take it
length ball on off, shows the full face of the bat to block the ball back to the bowler

commentTextItems.html: full ball outside off, drilled along the ground to long-off for a single
fullish ball outside off, gets a bit of an inside edge towards square leg to get off the strike
short of length, defended back towards the bowler off the backfoot
muscles it to the leg side, midwicket misfields, Bangladesh wanted two but Cremer comes in from long-on to keep them to one
in the blockhole, on middle and leg, punched to mid-on, single isn't taken again
Naeem keeps the strike by just dropping the ball towards point with soft hands, the batsmen zip through for a tight single, superb batting from Naeem

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c Junaid Siddique b Abdur Razzak 10 (22b 2x4 0x6 32m) SR: 45.45

dismissalComment.html: and "Junaid-man" is in action again as Razzak bowls one spinning away from the batsman. Masakadza is deceived in the flight as he comes down the track but decides to go through with the drive on the leg side. All he manages to get is an edge that flies fast to first slip where Junaid leaps across to his right and snips it mid-air. What a catch! and he has two of them to show off now

dismissalComment.html: a flighted delivery lures Raqibul out of the crease, he misses the ball and his struggle at the crease is over as Taylor whips off the bails

dismissalText.commentary: Shakib Al Hasan st Taylor b Matsikenyeri 20 (30b 2x4 0x6 66m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: Matsikenyeri has done it, superb delivery, Shakib is going down the track looking to smash the ball out of the ground, he doesn't connect as the ball spins away sharply, Taylor has ages to whip off the bails, no need for a third umpire this time

dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c Cremer b Matsikenyeri 23 (20b 2x4 1x6 20m) SR: 115

dismissalComment.html: Cremer takes the catch at backward square leg, it was a short ball, Mushfiqur goes for the sweep, top-edges it

dismissalText.commentary: Mahmudullah run out (Chibhabha) 33 (53b 1x4 1x6 73m) SR: 62.26

dismissalComment.html: is that a run-out? The Zimbabweans are confident, the batsman was well short at the non-striker's end when the stumps were broken, but did the bowler's hands disturb the stumps before that? it was turned to backward square leg, the batsmen looked to pinch a tight single, the replays showed that it was the ball that hit the stumps, Mahmudullah was well short, he's on his way, is there a twist in this game?
